      "span_text": "For example, [CITATION_1] observed that conidia of M. anisopliae var. acridum (syn. Metarhizium flavoviride) were generally the most resistant to artificial sunlight (295-1100 nm at a UVB irradiance of 0.3 W m -2 ) followed by conidia of B. bassiana, M. anisopliae and Paecilomyces fumosoroseus."
